	<text>
		<body>
			<p><pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-DEGOB1359_01.jpg"/> The persons in question have given us the following information: There were thirty Jewish
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">families</term> living in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/710858/chepa.html">Csepe</placeName>, they were farmers, craftsmen, tradesmen; most of them lived in
				financially sound circumstances. We had land and we also lived in wealth. One day after <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-754" type="subject">Passover</term> the Jewish inhabitants of the village
				were driven to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogue</term>, but we were
				sent home from there and we were told to collect our most necessary <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836"
					type="subject">clothes</term>, underwear and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject"
					>food</term>, then we were locked up in a barn. Two days later they took us to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>. In <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/688746/vynohradiv.html">Nagyszöllős</placeName> we spent the first 2-3 days in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogue</term>, where they <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-655" type="subject">deprived</term> us of all our more valuable
				belongings, then they took us to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>
				where we stayed for five weeks. <persName ref="#ehri_et_jarusil_jozsef">József Jarusil</persName>, village <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1112" type="subject">notary</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-200" type="subject">reported</term> against our father and based on that
				he was interned in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogue</term> as a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-969" type="subject">communist</term>. He was locked up there for five
				weeks, during which time he was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">beaten</term> very
				much and a stripe had been cut in his hair already in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545"
					type="subject">ghetto</term>. We set off to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2" type="camp"
					>Auschwitz</placeName> together with our father. As far as we know, nobody <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term> from the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> and those who <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> of natural causes, although they <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">beat</term> us very cruelly in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>, especially the wealthier people. The
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1124" type="subject">gendarmes</term> invented all sorts of
				tortures, they found fault with everything and they took every opportunity to treat us cruelly. So, for example, on one occasion the
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">men</term> tried to get some dry wood and the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1125" type="subject">gendarmes</term>, having noticed it, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">beat</term> them up brutally. They cut the hair of
				many <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">girls</term> completely; the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject">stripped naked</term> and <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">men</term> bared their heads. They lined everybody up already on the
				first day in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogue</term>. We were not
				allowed to look back; they threw stones at those who did. It was <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_hungarians"
					>Hungarian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1124" type="subject">gendarmes</term> who did all of this. <pb n="2"
					facs="EHRI-ET-DEGOB1359_02.jpg"/> They beat up even those who could not jump up from the stool when a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1125" type="subject">gendarme</term> came by. No complaint was taken
				against the work of the members of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-873" type="subject">Jewish
					council</term>. We did not have a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-855" type="subject">communal
					kitchen</term>, but those who ran out of supplies were given uncooked <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term>. After five weeks we were always told that
				we would go to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> on <placeName
					ref="#ehri_et_transdanubia">Transdanubia</placeName>, more precisely all the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">men</term> would. Before the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deportation</term> they had taken away all our papers
				in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogue</term>, they searched us and
				entrained us. They crammed 80 people in a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">cattle
					car</term>. They gave us some water and a bucket for a toilet too. Nobody <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745">died</term> in our <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">cattle car</term> and nobody <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term> from it either. When the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">Germans</term> took over us in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/724443/kosice.html">Kassa</placeName> we understood the situation already. After a three-day-long
				journey we arrived in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName> on 7th
				May. We were still in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">cattle car</term> when
					<term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoners</term><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">dressed in striped clothes</term> told us to get off
				and leave all our baggage there. After that they lined us up in rows of five and formed groups of us, one of which was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">sent</term> on the left, the other on the right hand
				side. They took us in the bathhouse and stripped us; they gave us grey <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoner‘s</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothes</term> and sent us to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">Camp</term> B. 700 of us were put in a block, 12 of us
				on a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">bunk</term>. Our provisions were the well-known
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">provisions</term>, and we had to line up for <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-487" type="subject">roll call</term> for hours in the morning and in the
				evening. We worked in a warehouse of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothes</term>;
				we were the ones to dress the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transports</term>. We
				took off the shoes of those who were <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411">selected</term>
				out from <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">Camp C</term> and if a person showed
				obstinacy or insisted on his <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836">shoes</term> very much
				we had to hit him, because if we did not, we were beaten up. We <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556"
					type="subject">worked</term> in day and night shifts; the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521"
					type="subject">transports</term> came to be dressed at night, but even from those <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transports</term> the weaker people were picked up and
				lined up naked in the courtyard. There was a strict block curfew when the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transports</term> were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selected</term>; we had to switch off the light and
				trucks came from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematorium</term> on which the
				naked people were put. We worked some metres away from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501"
					type="subject">crematorium</term>; from there we saw as the trucks were turned over and people were spilt from them to the burning
				pit like bags of potatoes. We often heard shouting, crying and moaning especially at night, when the voices reached us more easily,
				but we also saw fires and flames frequently. When a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject"
					>transport</term> from <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="camp"
					>Theresienstadt</placeName> arrived in <date when="1944-09">September</date> they took away <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> together. They led them to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematorium</term> in groups of five. In <date
					when="1944-09">September</date> there was a huge traffic there anyway; <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transports</term> came to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName> from other <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camps</term> too and those people were also quickly
				thrown into the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematorium</term>. There were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transports</term> coming from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Slovakia</placeName> still in <date when="1944-11">November</date>;
				these were not <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term> by <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">gas</term> but the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">mothers</term> with their small <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> were sent away and older boys and
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">men</term> were assigned to do some work. In
					<date when="1944-11">November</date>, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject"
					>crematorium</term> was dismantled; we also worked there for a week. They wanted every sign of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematorium</term> to disappear: even the bricks were
				carried away. In <date when="1944-12">December</date>, we were put in a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transport</term> as well and they took us to
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3087718/psie-pole.html">Hundsfeld</placeName> near <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3081368/wroclaw.html">Brezlau</placeName>. It took us one day to get there. We did somewhat better
				there, since it was a little <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> and the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">factory</term> provided us with <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">food</term>, so the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">provisions</term> were naturally better. Although we
				stayed there only for two weeks, then, as the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Russian
					troops</orgName> were approaching, they formed a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject"
					>transport</term> from us again and sent us to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-433" type="camp"
					>Gross Rosen</placeName>. <pb n="3" facs="EHRI-ET-DEGOB1359_03.jpg"/> The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">march</term> lasted for three days since it was <date
					when="1945-01">January</date>; there was a great snowstorm and it was terribly cold. We had to push big carts in which we were
				taking the belongings of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-478" type="subject">overseers</term>. One
				night we slept in a chamber; the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">ill</term> and weak
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> were taken after us on trucks,
				but we heard that some of them were taken off the truck to be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541"
					type="subject">shot dead</term>. They were buried right there in the snow. We had to help the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">ill</term> people to be taken off. We were very weak,
				we had nothing to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject">eat</term> and we were not able to
				pull the carts. We had to leave the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">ill</term>
				people’s cart there, so we left the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">ill</term> and
				we were being chased along. We were so exhausted already that we were not able to go any further; we would not have minded if they had
				shot us dead immediately. At last they took pity on us and, since we were not far away from our destination, they had the carts pulled
				to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> by horses. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-478" type="subject">SS women</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shot down</term> those <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> who collapsed from weakness with bone
				chilling coolness. 1,200 people started with the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject"
					>transport</term>, but by the time we arrived our number had been reduced to 700. The <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-433" type="camp">Gross Rosen</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> was only for <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">men</term>; there we received <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothes</term> and we had a rest for two weeks, then
				we continued our journey to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-570" type="camp"
				>Mauthausen</placeName>. There they took us to a bath for <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">men</term>, male <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoners</term> disinfected us, then we were given a
				pair of long <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">underpants</term> and a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">shirt</term>. There were no <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">women</term>’s <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothes</term> there. After three days we got our
				disinfected <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothes</term> back, but in the meantime
				the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Russians</orgName> came closer and there was no time to
				give everybody her own <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836">clothes</term>. We picked up
				the clothes at random and so we ran away like that, <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836"
					>dressed</term> improperly. We arrived in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp"
					>Bergen-Belsen</placeName> ten days later. On the way we lived on a little amount of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> that we had managed to bring with us.
				Several <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1105" type="subject">air raids</term> reached us on the way, but
				many of us <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject">hunger</term> too. We stayed in <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Bergen-Belsen</placeName> for three months. It was a
				collecting <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> and everybody was taken there
				from before the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Russians</orgName>. 1,200 of us were crammed
				in a block. We <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">slept</term> on the ground in filth
				and lice; we did not have blankets. We were given half a litre of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832"
					type="subject">soup</term> twice a day and a thin slice of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832"
					type="subject">bread</term> once in a while. At the end we did not even see a piece of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread</term> for weeks. We worked in the kitchen 18-20
				hours a day, so we sometimes managed to get hold of a few pieces of raw <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">carrots</term>. The <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004291">English troops</orgName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberated</term> us on <date when="1945-04-15">15th
					April</date> and soon they took us to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp"
					>Bergen</placeName>. They <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">accommodated</term> us
				in a garrison of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>. There we had a good
				place, nice treatment and proper <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">provisions</term>.
				The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">ill</term> people received medical treatment.
				From there they took us to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2804856/zelle.html">Celle</placeName>, then with a <term
					type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_czechs">Czech</term> transport we came home. Two <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">men</term> were assigned to escort us in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Pozsony</placeName>, thus we came home through <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3049519/komarom.html">Komárom</placeName>. Our plans for the future: we would like <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-203" type="subject">to go to</term>
				<placeName ref="#ehri_et_palestine">Palestine</placeName> soon.</p>
		</body>
	</text>
